com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel

Interface GIModelFactory


  • @NotThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface GIModelFactory
    A GIModelFactory provides methods to instantiate both model types (BswmdModel and DefRef API) seamlessly.

    The general use case for the client is to create ONE factory at the start of the generation process and calling GIModelFactory.getInstance(Class, MIHasDefinition) for each IPredefinedVariantView and each GIModuleConfiguration, and then discard the factory.

    Attention: DO NOT reuse the factory instance over Generation execution runs!

    A GIModelFactory also supports multi variant bsmwd models for the Post-build selectable access for e.g. code generation in a Generator. The GIModelFactory caches the active view during the Model creation and delegates to the correct GeneratorModelAccess class for each active variant. This allows the navigate to different views via GIModelObject.

    With DefinitionTyped (generated) ModelFactory

    Every DefinitionTyped BswmdModel has its own factory <Module>ModelFactory which provides a method get<Module>ModuleConfig() to get a module configuration. 
     
 final CanIfModelFactory factory = CanIfModelFactory.createFactory(generatorPackage);

 final CanIf canIfModule = factory.getCanIfModuleConfig();
    A DefinitionTyped ModelFactory can be used for each type of elements (module configurations, container, parameter) and will create definition typed element if possible before it creates untyped elements. So when you request a CanIfModelFactory to create a CanIfContainer you will get an instance of CanIfContainer, but if you request a ComContainer and this container is not generated in the CanIf model you will get an instance of GIContainer.

    DefinitionTyped ModelFactory without generator (e.g. old automation use case)

    You can use the generated ModelFactories also without a generator according to the untyped factories. So an automation client can instantiate a BswmdModel although the client has no IGeneratorPackage.

    Note: You could use the method GModelFactory#createFactory(com.vector.cfg.gen.core.moduleinterface.IGeneratorPackageReferable) to create a GIModelFactory for an "untyped" bswmd model.

      • getAllInstancesForAllPostBuildVariants

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends GIModelObject> java.util.List<T> getAllInstancesForAllPostBuildVariants(java.lang.Class<T> giModelClazz,
                                                                                                     DefRef defRefOfRequestedElement)
        The method getAllInstancesForAllPostBuildVariants() returns all instances of the DefRef in the project, for each Post-build selectable variant in the project. The returned type in the BswmdModel instance of the passed class (giModelClazz).

        If the project has no variant, the IUnfilteredView is used.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the generic type
        Parameters:
        giModelClazz - The BswmdModel class.
        defRefOfRequestedElement - the DefRef of requested elements.
        Returns:
        the all instances of type DefRef for all post build variants, or IUnfilteredView.

        The method getAllInstancesForAllPostBuildVariants(Class, MIHasDefinition) returns all instances of the mdfCfgElement, for each Post-build selectable variant in the project. The returned type in the BswmdModel instance of the passed class (giModelClazz). You get al list containing a BswmdModel instance of the IModelView in which the passed MDF element (mdfCfgElement) is visible.

        If the project has no variant, the IUnfilteredView is used.

        R - the generic type
        Parameters:
